See test case below:

```json
# curl -H "Content-Type: application/json" -XPUT http://10.35.25.164:9222/test_dd?pretty -d '
{
   "mappings": {
      "_doc": {
         "properties": {
            "k1": {
               "type": "long"
            }
         }
      }
   }
}'

# curl -H "Content-Type: application/json" -XPUT http://10.35.25.164:9222/test_dd/_doc/1?pretty -d '{}'

```

In DEBUG build mode, if we read the es index, **RAPIDJSON_ASSERT**
will be triggered because `hits.hits.fields` does not exist.

```
# curl -H "Content-Type: application/json" -XPOST '10.35.25.164:9222/test_dd/_doc/_search?filter_path=_scroll_id,hits.total,hits.hits._score,hits.hits.fields&pretty' -d '{"query":{"match_all":{}},"stored_fields":"_none_","docvalue_fields":["k1"]}'
{
  "hits" : {
    "total" : 1,
    "hits" : [
      {
        "_score" : null
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

## Types of changes

What types of changes does your code introduce to Doris?
